narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned a lot about musical elements such as harmony, melody, and rhythm. I learned how to read sheet music and learned some music theory on how/why things sound good.

General understanding of basic music theory, with an emphasis on solfege, which helped teach core concepts. Modes, keys, time signatures, meter, subdivisions, harmony, chords, and some experience with composition (which I really liked).
I began my journey with music theory, understanding the little things and the big
I learned how to read basic music, analyze harmonies, and understand solfege and pitch.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The canvas assignments can be much at times, as well as the other assignments it can be something that you have to be diligent on.
I loved the course as a whole, but I'd suggest integrating more assignments where we compose our own music!

strengths: material is pretty easy to comprehend, lots of practice opportunities, quick homework, very few expectations for class preparation, reasonable midterm & final
weaknesses: singing in class gets boring and repetitive
I really enjoyed the course and thought it was taught in a very good order

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would recommend this course to any student regardless of musical background or training. It is really fun to sing and there is no pressure of being an expert. Prof. Hallie was truly exceptional !
Definitely, it gives a good grounding in theory and serves as a jumping point for further skills development.

YES! I learned more than I ever thought I could in a semester of class. The material is very engaging and the class environment is extremely supportive/conducive to learning for individuals of all backgrounds.
Yes! If you are interested in music and want to learn more, this is a great class!
